COVID-19 test AFP/Georg Hochmuth JOHANNESBURG -The Department of Health has reported that South Africa has recorded 18,000 new COVID-19 infections in the last 24 hours. READ: COVID-19 in SA: When can we expect the vaccine? This marks another record number of cases recorded in a single day. 436 people have died of COVID-19 since the last report. The number of recoveries is 879 671. As of today the cumulative total of #COVID19 cases identified is 1 057 161 with 18 000 cases identified since the last report. A cumulative 6 609 208 tests have done. 55 447 new tests done. There are 436 more COVID-19 related deaths.Number of recoveries is 879 671. pic.twitter.com/ycrKBQijIt